TY  - JOUR
T1  - Econometrics and Management Science: Their Overlap and Interaction
AU  - Thiel, H.
Y1  - 1965/06/01
PY  - 1965
DA  - 1965/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.11.8.B200
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.11.8.B200
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-200
EP  - B-212
VL  - 11
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This is an expository article on the relationship of econometrics and management science. After some general observations it considers a number of applications, such as prediction on the basis of input-output models and of econometric macromodels and decision-making based on linear decision rules. These rules are applied to cost minimization in a factory and welfare maximization for a country as a whole. In the last part of the paper some attention is paid to uncertainty problems with respect to the constraints subject to which maximization or minimization takes place.
AB  - This is an expository article on the relationship of econometrics and management science. After some general observations it considers a number of applications, such as prediction on the basis of input-output models and of econometric macromodels and decision-making based on linear decision rules. These rules are applied to cost minimization in a factory and welfare maximization for a country as a whole. In the last part of the paper some attention is paid to uncertainty problems with respect to the constraints subject to which maximization or minimization takes place.
